description.narrative: Established in 2003 in Geneva, Switzerland, DNDi’s headquarters is active in Research & Development activities, as well as in administrative and support functions, including Finance, Human Resources, IT, Policy, Advocacy, Communications and External Relations.

Teams manage projects and partnerships so that new and adapted treatments are developed for neglected patients and people with neglected tropical diseases such as sleeping sickness, leishmaniasis, Chagas disease, paediatric HIV, filarial diseases, mycetoma, hepatitis C, and others. From 2016 until 2018, DNDi Geneva incubated the WHO-DNDi joint initiative Global Antibiotic Research & Development Partnership (GARDP), a not-for-profit research and development organization developing and delivering new or improved antibiotic treatments, now functioning as an independent entity.
